{"comments":"PerlinNoise - classic gradient noise configuration.\n\nKen Perlin's gradient noise algorithm (1983/2002), the foundation of\nprocedural texture generation. Produces smooth, natural-looking random\npatterns without the harsh edges of value noise.\n\n## Composition\n\nA molecule composed from Material pillar atoms:\n- NoiseFrequency: spatial frequency (0.0 to finite)\n- NoiseAmplitude: output range (0.0 to 1.0)\n- NoiseSeed: deterministic seed (any Int)\n\n## Usage\n\n```purescript\n-- Subtle texture noise\nsubtle = perlinNoise\n  { frequency: NoiseFrequency.standard\n  , amplitude: NoiseAmplitude.subtle\n  , seed: NoiseSeed.zero\n  }\n\n-- Turbulent cloud-like noise\nturbulent = perlinNoiseTurbulent\n  { frequency: noiseFrequency 2.0\n  , amplitude: noiseAmplitude 0.8\n  , seed: noiseSeed 42\n  }\n```\n\n## Performance\n\nPerlin noise is O(2^n) where n is dimensions. 2D is fast, 3D is moderate.\nFor better performance with similar quality, consider SimplexNoise.\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Hydrogen.Schema.Surface.NoiseFrequency\n- Hydrogen.Schema.Surface.NoiseAmplitude\n- Hydrogen.Schema.Surface.NoiseSeed\n","declarations":[{"children":[{"comments":null,"info":{"arguments":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["frequency",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Surface","NoiseFrequency"],"NoiseFrequency"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["amplitude",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Surface","NoiseAmplitude"],"NoiseAmplitude"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["seed",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Surface","NoiseSeed"],"NoiseSeed"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["turbulent",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Boolean"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}],"declType":"dataConstructor"},"sourceSpan":{"end":[104,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Surface/PerlinNoise.purs","start":[99,21]},"title":"PerlinNoise"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Eq"],"Eq"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Surface","PerlinNoise"],"PerlinNoise"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[106,48],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Surface/PerlinNoise.purs","start":[106,1]},"title":"eqPerlinNoise"},{"comments":null,"info":{"declType":"instance","dependencies":[],"type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Data","Show"],"Show"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Surface","PerlinNoise"],"PerlinNoise"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"sourceSpan":{"end":[114,13],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Surface/PerlinNoise.purs","start":[108,1]},"title":"showPerlinNoise"}],"comments":"PerlinNoise - gradient noise configuration molecule.\n\nDescribes the parameters needed to generate Perlin noise.\nThis is pure data — actual noise generation happens at the runtime boundary.\n","info":{"dataDeclType":"newtype","declType":"data","roles":[],"typeArguments":[]},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[104,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Surface/PerlinNoise.purs","start":[99,1]},"title":"PerlinNoise"},{"children":[],"comments":"Configuration record for creating PerlinNoise\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["frequency",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Surface","NoiseFrequency"],"NoiseFrequency"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["amplitude",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema",